wer, and status in a society – play an important role in ethnic and nationalist conflict. Bringing together international experts on the politics of ethnicity and nationalism, this final volume in the prestigious EDG series investigates how moral economies have been challenged in identity-based communities in ways that precipitate or exacerbate conflicts. The combination of theoretical chapters and case studies ranging from Africa and Asia to North America provides compelling evidence for the value of moral economy analysis in understanding problems associated with ethnic and nationalist mobilization and conflict.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aEconomicsxMoral and ethical aspects. 0aEconomicsxPolitical aspects. 0aEthnicityxPolitical aspects. 0aEthnicity. 0aNationalismxPolitical aspects. 0aNationalism. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Globalization.2bisacsh1 aAbu-Laban, Yasmeen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBerman, Bruce J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBerman, Bruce J., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aDoucet, Leslie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHaklai, Oded, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHughes, Lotte, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHunter, Emma, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLaliberté, André, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLaliberté, André, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aLarin, Stephen J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLarin, Stephen J., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aLitalien, Manuel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.lo